programme.title: Voile : Spirit of Yachting S3 (n°1)
programme.desc: The Rolex China Sea Race returns to the sailing calendar after a five-year absence. This Asian blue-water classic commences on April 5th from Hong Kong's iconic harbour and takes competitors 565 nautical miles across the South China Sea to Subic Bay in the Philippines. 2023 marks the 61st anniversary of this biennial Offshore Category 1 Race organised by the Royal Hong Kong Yacht Club. An international fleet will be attempting to break the Monohull Race Record of 47 hours 31m 08s set in 2016.
